OL,3,CLidl employee unfairly dismissed for
OL,4,Cnot having a degree is awarded #50k
OL,6,FA Lidl employee who felt "punished for
OL,7,Fgrowing up on a Welsh council estate"
OL,8,Fby redundancy criteria was unfairly
OL,9,Fdismissed and has been awarded #50,926
OL,10,Fby a tribunal.
OL,12,FWayne Norman, aged 63, had been
OL,13,Fworking for the supermarket chain for
OL,14,Fjust under 23 years when he was
OL,15,Fdismissed because he didn't have a
OL,16,Fdegree or qualification, in a round of
OL,17,Fredundancies.
