OL,3,CLidl employee unfairly dismissed for
OL,4,Cnot having a degree is awarded #50k
OL,6,FIn a written ruling, employment Judge
OL,7,FNeil Maidment said Mr Norman had felt
OL,8,F"discredited" because he did not have
OL,9,Fa degree and "punished" for the fact
OL,10,Fhe had grown up on a Welsh council
OL,11,Festate and had not had the opportunity
OL,12,Fto attend university.
OL,14,FOf Mr Norman's evidence, the judge
OL,15,Fwrote: "He said that he had always
OL,16,Fbelieved that if you work hard enough,
OL,17,Flong enough and successfully enough
OL,18,Fyou will be rewarded and respected for
OL,19,Fthe work you do.
