OL,3,CLidl employee unfairly dismissed for
OL,4,Cnot having a degree is awarded #50k
OL,6,F"Being told that he was marked down
OL,7,Fbecause he didn't have a degree made
OL,8,Fhim feel inadequate and demeaned.
OL,10,FHe described growing up on a North
OL,11,FWales council estate in the 1960s and
OL,12,F1970s when there was no opportunity
OL,13,Ffor someone like him to go to
OL,14,Funiversity.
OL,16,F"He felt punished for this and angry.
OL,17,FHis parents had done their best to
OL,18,Fprovide everything for him and he had
OL,19,Fworked his way up the ladder."
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU{D@^O]
