OL,3,CLidl employee unfairly dismissed for
OL,4,Cnot having a degree is awarded #50k
OL,6,FMr Schofield's evidence was not
OL,7,F"wholly consistent" regarding the
OL,8,Fsignificance of a qualification or
OL,9,Fdegree during the redundancy process,
OL,10,Fthe tribunal ruled.
OL,12,FDuring his time at Lidl, Mr Norman had
OL,13,Fgot on well with his colleagues with a
OL,14,Ffeeling that they were "very much part
OL,15,Fof a family", the tribunal heard.
