OL,3,CLidl employee unfairly dismissed for
OL,4,Cnot having a degree is awarded #50k
OL,6,FHad it not been for his dismissal, the
OL,7,Fclaimant "envisaged himself happily
OL,8,Fworking on with the respondent until
OL,9,Faround his 67th birthday", Judge
OL,10,FMaidment wrote.
OL,12,FThe tribunal ruled that the "failure
OL,13,Fto conduct a reasonable process of
OL,14,Fconsultation" was sufficient enough to
OL,15,Frender the dismissal unfair and, while
OL,16,Fthe respondent had set up a
OL,17,F"potentially fair" scoring and
OL,18,Fcriteria method, the tribunal could
OL,19,Fnot conclude that this was "fairly and
OL,20,Freasonably" applied in Mr Norman's
OL,21,Fcase.
