OL,3,CLidl employee unfairly dismissed for
OL,4,Cnot having a degree is awarded #50k
OL,6,FMr Norman's complaint of direct age
OL,7,Fdiscrimination failed as the tribunal
OL,8,Faccepted he had been selected for
OL,9,Fredundancy based on an assessment of
OL,10,Fhis "abilities unrelated to age" and
OL,11,Fthere was "no evidence" that his
OL,12,F"likely longevity" in the role or age
OL,13,Fmay affect his performance.
OL,15,FHis further claim of age-related
OL,16,Fharassment, including an allegation
OL,17,Fthat a colleague had referred to him
OL,18,Fas "grandad" in the office, also
OL,19,Ffailed.
